13 WHEREAS, Mr. Rucker, a physical therapist assistant student from Athens Technical
14 College, enrolled to receive the very best training necessary to acquire the knowledge and
15 skills that will afford him a secure future in his chosen profession; and
16 WHEREAS, Mr. Rucker will serve as an ambassador for technical education in Georgia,
17 representing more than 148,000 TCSG students who benefit from technical education
18 programs at colleges throughout the state; and
19 WHEREAS, in pursuing his education, Mr. Rucker brought honor to himself, his family,
20 Athens Technical College, and the entire Technical College System of Georgia, which he
21 represents as Georgia's outstanding technical college student for 2024.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
23 the members of this body congratulate and commend Mr. Nicholas Rucker for his
24 outstanding achievements and efforts to promote technical education in Georgia as well as
25 extend best wishes for continued success.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
27 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Mr.
28 Nicholas Rucker.
